text: Acanthophila latipennella is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It is found in south-eastern Siberia and Europe, where it has been recorded from Norway south to Italy and east to Russia.Fauna Europaea The wingspan is .lepiforum.de The larvae feed on Picea abies. ==References== Category:Acanthophila Category:Moths described in 1937 Category:Moths of Europe Category:Moths of Russia
